2012 Ithaca Grand Prix of Cyclocross PRESENTED BY
University of Michigan Mountain Bike Cup
SwampThingCX #1
course:
The race will take place at Lansing\'s 60-acre Red Cedar Park, a former golf course that has been unused and unmaintained since 2007. In 2011, we started cutting a cyclocross course into the overgrown vegetation, and that fall put on the first cyclocross racing Lansing had seen in years. Since then, the park - while still unmaintained by the city - has become an unofficial cyclocross park. Situated near Michigan State University and not far from the Capitol building, the park is a beautiful swath of nature in the middle of the city.

Each lap of the course is approximately 1.6 miles in length and incorporates grass, dirt, pavement, mud, and barriers as it makes its way through fields and woods along the Red Cedar river.
registration:
Early registration is $25. Same day registration is $30.
Additional races on the same day are only $10.
Award presentation and prize raffle for all categories will follow the end of the last wave.
Prizes for top 3 finishers in each category.
Elite Men $200/3
Elite Women $150/3
directions:
Red Cedar Park
203 South Clippert Street
Lansing, MI
http://g.co/maps/hhb4v

2012 TREK Breast Cancer Awareness Ride
description:
On October 14th 2012, Rochester Bike Shop will host the 6th annual Trek Women Breast Cancer Awareness ride. Featuring 10- and 25-mile family-friendly group rides, the event donates registration fees directly to The Breast Cancer Research Foundation
Held Under USA Cycling Event Permit
course: The course will be a marked, out and back route held on the Pain Creek trail. The 10 mile option will turn around at the Gunn Rd bridge. The 20 mile option will go to Lake Orion. A support tent with beverages and snacks at the turn around point.
registration:
http://www.active.com/cycling/rochester-mi/trek-breast-cancer-awareness-ride-rochester-bike-shop-2012

Both on site and online registration will remain opened up until ride start! Cash, check or credit card will be accepted. Please make checks written to The Breast Cancer Research Foundation.
notes: This is not a race! So relax, take you time and have lots of fun!!
directions: The event will be held in downtown Rochester. The small parking lot south of University between East St and Water.
